The paper deals with the problem of achieving secrecy in communication networks with untrusted relays, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of compress-and-forward techniques, which is a common approach in network coding (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper considers specific channel models, such as the Gaussian channel, which is relevant to multimedia communication (cs.MM).
